LONG="
Netcat is a simple Unix utility which reads and writes data across network 
connections, using TCP or UDP protocol. It is designed to be a reliable 
backend tool that can be used directly or easily driven by other programs 
time, it is a feature-rich network debugging and exploration tool, since it 
can create almost any kind of connection you would need and has several 
interesting built-in capabilities.
"
